                            <comment id="26866" author="niklas@trillian.se" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2007 01:56:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess I should have said that we have a forest like structure. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I.e. potentially multiple trees. Nodes can be moved between trees and can become root nodes in a tree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="34384" author="balex" created="Fri, 4 Apr 2008 19:16:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Verified JdbcMutableAclService.updateObjectIdentity(MutableAcl) supports modifying the parent. So this should work without any significant changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Accordingly, AclImpl.setParent(Acl) changed to allow null parents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SVN committed revision 2867.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
